<HEADLINE> Widespread Damage Reported in Quebec after </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- A boy of nine years old was killed
and two others were injured in an overnight storm, which has also
caused widespread damage in the Montreal area of Quebec, reports
reaching here said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Hydro-Quebec reported power interruption to about 450,000
customers in the area, where uprooted trees and several fires were
also witnessed.
</P>
<P>
Roof ripped off and boats flipped over and scattered about the
water-side were shown in the coverage of the local television
station, which said later storms are yet to come.  
</P>
