<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Launches Investment Guide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Investment
Authority Monday said an investment guide designed to enhance the
inflows of foreign direct investment to Ethiopia was launched in
Geneva, Switzerland on the same day.
</P>
<P>
General Manager of the authority Tadesse Haile told press here
that the investment guide, which would be distributed to foreign
investors around the globe, featured the economic and political
landscape of Ethiopia as well as the prevailing investment
environment and opportunities in the country.
</P>
<P>
The guide would promote the favorable investment image of
Ethiopia and help attract foreign capital, trade, investment and
technology to it, he added.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's endeavors to achieve socio-economic transformation
coupled with the promising democratization process had enabled the
country to get the support of the the United Nations Conference on
Trade and Development (UNCTAD) and the International Chamber of
Commerce, the general manager noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that Ethiopia is one of the six least developed
countries supported by the afore-mentioned international
organizations to prepare an investment guide. Bangladesh,
Madagascar, Mali, Mozambique and Uganda are the remaining five
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
