<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Confidence in UK Remains High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON July 5 (Xinhua) - Britain remains the top market in
Europe for foreign direct investment (FDI), according to the
latest FDI Conference Index released here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The six monthly survey of CEOs, CFOs and other top executives
of Global 1000 companies compares the relative likelihood of
direct investment in 60 countries over the next one to three
years.
</P>
<P>
The latest report shows that the UK moved up one place to
third overall, behind the US and China.
</P>
<P>
The next highest placed European country in the survey was
Poland in 8th place, with Germany 9th, France 10th and Italy 11th.
</P>
</TEXT>
