<HEADLINE> UK Insurance Markets Unite To Improve Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Britain's two main insurance markets
have set up a joint top level forum to achieve radical changes in
business processes.
</P>
<P>
Both Lloyd's and the International Underwriting Association of
London have actively encouraged the development of e-commerce,
including the recent establishment of an international insurance
business cerner, WESE.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here Monday, Max Taylor,
Chairman of Lloyd's said: "The aim is to ensure that London
retains and enhances its position as the world's foremost
insurance marketplace."
</P>
<P>
By streamlining processes and making full use of electronic
commerce to the benefit of customers, intermediaries and
underwriters, London will keep its position as it enjoys now, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The forum will concentrate on four areas:
</P>
<P>
- The payment of claims, the issuance of policies and the
payment of premiums - the objective being to ensure the shortest
possible delivery time in each case.
</P>
<P>
- The setting of ambitious service standards in a number of key
areas. Statistics will be published showing the performance of
brokers, underwriters and central services against these agreed
standards.
</P>
<P>
- Supporting existing and new initiatives to improve access for
brokers to the London market by simplifying procedures, adopting
international processing standards.
</P>
<P>
- The promotion and early adoption of e-commerce and electronic
trading.
</P>
<P>
The forum has promised to work closely with the leaders of the
broking community in London to achieve their aims. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
