<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, Monday. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA -- A senior Palestinian official has rejected a recent
U.S. proposal to compensate Palestinian refugees in lieu of their
return home.
</P>
<P>
In an interview broadcast Monday by the Voice of Palestine,
deputy head of the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) Mahmoud
Abbas (also known as Abu Mazen) said the proposal was not new.
</P>
<P>
He said the return of refugees to their homes is a legitimate
right and the issue will come up for discussion during the final
status negotiations between the Palestinians and Israel.
(BC-Palestinians-Refugees)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- One person was killed and 10 others injured in two
landmine explosions in southeastern Turkey on Monday.
</P>
<P>
A landmine, planted by militants of the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK), exploded Monday when a minibus pressed it
near Uzumlu village in Durankaya town of Hakkari province,
leaving one person dead and five others, including three village
guards, injured.
</P>
<P>
In another development, a vehicle belonging to the Turkish
Petroleum Corporation hit a landmine also planted by the PKK
rebels in Batman province Sunday night, injuring five, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported. (BC-Turkey-PKK)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister-elect Ehud Barak officially
wrapped up six-week-plus coalition talks Monday and will present
his cabinet list to the Knesset (parliament) for approval Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The incoming seven-faction coalition comprises One Israel, the
ultra-Orthodox Shas Party, the United Torah Judaism, Meretz, the
Center Party, the Russian immigrants party Yisrael b'Aliya and
National Religious Party. (BC-Israel-Coalition)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- The minister of petroleum and mineral resources of
the United Arab Emirates (UAE) Monday cautioned main oil producers
against increasing production, saying that they would not benefit
for long if they did so.
</P>
<P>
"It is not in the interest of producing countries to exploit
the current improvement in the price of oil to increase their
production during this period," said Obeid Bin Saif Al Nassiri.
(BC-UAE-Oil Production) 
</P>
</TEXT>
