<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets Soars On deals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 5 (Xinhua) -- European markets all surged to
strong closing gains Monday as upbeat economic figures, strong
overseas markets and a spurt in oil stocks spurred the market.
</P>
<P>
While volumes remained low on a day when the New York market
was closed for U.S. independence celebrations, the FTSE closed up
100.1 points at 6592, just seven points short of a record close.
</P>
<P>
Strong performances in the Far East markets overnight set
London off to a bullish start followed by promising service
industry figures showing the sector booming.
</P>
<P>
Germany's electronic Xetra Dax enjoyed an even stronger
session, as it closed at a second consecutive year-high, despite
the lack of specific bid talk.
</P>
<P>
The index leapt 106.57 points to end at 5625.62, a rise of 1.93
percent as investors took heart from the positive picture painted
by the monthly services sector survey.
</P>
<P>
Paris stocks set new record closing high lifted by the prospect
of a mega-merger in French oil sector as TotalFina makes a 42bn
euros hostile bid for Elf.
</P>
<P>
The Cac 40 closed up 1.67 percent at 4697.84. Elf - which made
over two-thirds of Cac's 77.2 points rise - closed up 21.52
percent at 177.3 euros. 
</P>
</TEXT>
