<HEADLINE> UNHCR Office: 550,000 Kosovo Refugees Return Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Some 550,000 refugees have returned
to Kosovo since June 13, said the office of the United Nations
High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Among these refugees, 316,000 were from Albania, 189,000 from
Macedonia, and 42,500 from Montenegro, the office said. They found
sanctuary in Albania, Macedonia and Montenegro months ago, it
added.
</P>
<P>
Some of them went back to Kosovo themselves, and some were sent
back under an organized repatriation plan sponsored by the UNHCR,
which started last Thursday, according to the office.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian Telegraphic Agency reported last Thursday that
some 279,000 Kosovars in Albania had returned home, but there were
still 170,000 staying in Albania up to the day.
</P>
<P>
General John Reith, commander of the NATO forces in Albania,
Sunday said in northern Albania that he believed that the
resettlement of Kosovo refugees could end by September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
