<HEADLINE> Generals, Brigadier Generals Promoted in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia announced Monday that
three brigadier generals and five colonels have been promoted to
generals and brigadier generals respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted a directive from President
Negasso Gidada as saying that Brigadier Generals Abebe
Tekle-Haiyanot, Abadula Gemeda and Samora Yenus have been promoted
to generals on July 1, 1999. Abebe Tekle-Haiyanot is the Commander
of Air Force.
</P>
<P>
The new promotions happened when Ethiopia's border war with
Eritrea is going on, and this meant to boost the moral of the
Ethiopian officers and men, Observers here say.
</P>
<P>
The promotions brought the total generals in the Horn of
African country to four. General Tsadkan Gebre Tensay, Chief of
Staff of the Ethiopian Defense Forces, was promoted to the highest
rank of general in February 1996.
</P>
<P>
The five newly promoted brigadier generals are Colonels Gezai
Abera, Berhane Negash, Tadesse Berehe, Se'are Mekonnen and
Tadesse Worede. These have brought the total brigadier generals
in the country to 14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
