<HEADLINE> Iran Urged to Positively Respond to GCC Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League on Monday urged Iran
to positively respond to the efforts made by the Gulf Cooperation
Council (GCC) to help resolve its territorial disputes with the
United Arab Emirates (UAE).
</P>
<P>
The league said in a statement that "it is closely watching the
developments of the issue over three Gulf islands," which it said
are UAE territories but under Iranian occupation.
</P>
<P>
The 22-nation pan-Arab forum said it also noticed the support
expressed by the GCC for UAE's right to "peaceful restoration of
the islands."
</P>
<P>
The GCC is a regional political and economic alliance which
comprises Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia and the UAE.
It set up a committee on Saturday to help solve the disputes over
the islands of Greater Tunb, Lesser Tunb and Abu Musa near the
strategic Strait of Hormuz.
</P>
<P>
Reaching a solution to the problem in line with international
law and good neighborliness would enhance the Arab-Iranian ties
for the regional security and stability, the statement stressed.
</P>
<P>
While the UAE and Iran both claim the three Gulf islands, the
two countries have voiced readiness to resolve the disputes
through peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
Abu Dhabi calls for a solution through international
arbitration while Tehran prefers bilateral negotiations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
