<HEADLINE> Italy to Provide Assistance on Cyprus' EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and Italy Monday agreed on
ways of promoting cooperation regarding the island's harmonization
with the acquis communautaire.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken during a meeting in Italy between
Cyprus' chief negotiator in the accession talks with the European
Union, George Vassiliou, and the Italian minister for EU policy,
Enrico Letta, the Cyprus News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Italy will grant practical assistance to Cyprus in relation to
the island's harmonization with the acquis communautaire on a
number of issues including taxation.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation will be sealed during Letta's visit to Cyprus
later this month.
</P>
<P>
A number of meetings between Italian and Cypriot experts on
relevant issues will also be held.
</P>
<P>
Vassiliou, who is visiting Italy, Monday met President of
the Italian Parliamentary Committee for EU Policy Antonio Ruberti.
</P>
<P>
Ruberti said the Italian parliament supports Cyprus' accession.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus applied for EU membership in July 1990. It began
substansive accession talks in November 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
