<HEADLINE> Regionalization Must Be Attended to: Mozambican </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Foreign Minister Leonardo
Simao said Monday regionalization must be included in the agenda
of globalization because the economic globalization has not given
an answer to many questions raised by the southern hemisphere.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of globalization doesn't include such issues as
poverty elimination, stability promotion and welfare realization,
the minister said, while opening the conference on the cooperation
and integration in southern Africa here.
</P>
<P>
The globalization has not responded to the actual demand of the
Third World people, Simao said, adding: all signs indicate that
the next millenium will begin with the conflict between
globalization and regionalization.
</P>
<P>
The minister called upon participants at the two-day conference
to pay special attention to the analysis of the problems
concerning regionalization.
</P>
<P>
If the desires and aspirations of the people in this region
would not be attended to, then the regional economic integration
will become the tool for the region to achieve their social and
economic interests, said Simao.
</P>
<P>
The conference will also focus on such topics as the Basis of
the Regional Integration in Southern Africa and the Integration of
the Emerging Markets in Southern Africa, Asia and Latin America.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was sponsored by the Strategic and International
Studies Center of the Superior Institute of the International
Relations of Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
Besides experts, diplomats in Maputo and members of the
Mozambican parliament were also attending the meeting which will
be closed Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
