<HEADLINE> China Lodges Strong Protest against "Diplomatic Ties" between PNG and Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has lodged a
strong protest with the Papua New Guinean government over its
signing of a communique on the establishment of "diplomatic ties"
with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by Chinese Foreign Ministry spokeswoman
Zhang Qiyue here tonight when asked to comment on the move.
</P>
<P>
PNG Foreign Minister Roy Yaki signed earlier today with Taiwan'
s "Foreign Minister" Jason Hu a communique on the formation of "
diplomatic ties" between PNG and Taiwan during PNG Prime Minister
Bill Skate's visit to Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that the Chinese side strongly urges the Papua New
Guinean government to correct its erroneous decision in signing
such a communique with Taiwan in order to bring the bilateral ties
between China and PNG back onto a normal track. "Otherwise, the
Papua New Guinean government must bear all responsibilities for
the serious consequences arising therefrom," she said.
</P>
<P>
She noted that it is widely acknowledged that there is only one
China in the world and the Government of the People's Republic of
China is the sole legal government of China and Taiwan is an
inalienable part of China.
</P>
<P>
"The PNG government's move of signing such a communique has
entirely violated its commitment towards the 'one China' policy,"
she said, adding that the move constitutes a serious infringement
of China's sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
"The act has also seriously damaged the long term friendly ties
between China and PNG," she added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
