<HEADLINE> Swedish Striker Martin Dahlin Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Swedish international Martin
Dahlin called it quits on Monday citing back injury preventing him
from playing aggressively.
</P>
<P>
"I have played my last match, scored my last goal and elbowed
my last opponent," the talented striker told a news conference.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old also ruled out the possibility that he would
accept offers of some clubs for his chronic back injury after he
was released from Blackburn Rovers of the Premier League.
</P>
<P>
"I have done all I can to get 100 percent fit again, and will
be able to live a normal life. But the back injury prevents me
playing aggressively and I therefore chose to retire."
</P>
<P>
Dahlin, a member of the third-placed Sweden at the 1994 World
Cup finals, notched 29 goals during 60 international appearances.
</P>
<P>
He played for several European clubs including the German
Bundesliga side Borussia Moenchengladbach and Italy's Roma.
</P>
</TEXT>
