<HEADLINE> Euro Sags to New Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The euro sank to another new low on
Monday, with the European Central Bank issuing a reference rate of
1.0232 dollars, down from 1.0241 dollars on last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The rate corresponded to 1.9115 marks per dollar, compared with
Friday's 1.9098 marks.
</P>
<P>
But the euro was steady against other major currencies, with
only marginal changes: 0.6491 pounds sterling (0.6498), 125.18 yen
(123.93) and 1.6055 Swiss francs (1.6060).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile German shares continued their strong resurgence in
the wake of last week's decision by the U.S. Federal Reserve to
raise interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The 30-share DAX Index broke through the 5,600-point barrier
for the first time in eight months, rising 106.57 points to the
day's high 5,625.62 points. the secondary 70-share M-DAX finished
56.16 points higher at 4,128.66 points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
