<HEADLINE> Pakistan Asks India to Return Eight Personnel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Monday demanded the
return of its eight-men patrol that lost contact with its base
during the military conflict along the Line of Control (LoC),
saying one of them is being paraded on Indian electronic media.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier Rashid Qureshi, director general of the
Inter-Services Public Relations, told journalists that till Monday
Pakistan has no information from India about the fate of the eight
army men.
</P>
<P>
"In fact today we demand the return of these eight personnel,
one of whom they are now parading in front of cameras as someone
captured a couple of days ago," he said.
</P>
<P>
Qureshi said the Indians have these men in custody and it
should inform Pakistan of their fate.
</P>
<P>
He said it has been a long time since the eight men were
captured. "It is reasonable to assume that they have either been
killed or kept under custody by the Indians."
</P>
<P>
Qureshi told journalists at a news briefing in late June that a
Pakistani patrol had lost contact with its base on June 12 or June
13 during an Indian attack at the Line of Control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
