<HEADLINE> Angolan Authoress Wins Portuguese Culture Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Angolan authoress Gabriela Antunes
has won the 1999 Culture Award from the Cultural Foundation of the
Portuguese Language in Portugal, the Angolan News Agency Angog
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The judges of the foundation said that they have decided to
issue the award to Antunes, a child educator and authoress, for
her prominent contribution to preserving the culture of the
Portuguese language.
</P>
<P>
Gabriela Antunes was born in Angola's central province of
Huambo in 1937.
</P>
<P>
She won her bachelor degree in linguistics in the University of
Germany.
</P>
<P>
Her works include A Guide,The Garden of Anita, and The
Punishment of A Dragon.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese foundation said that it will announce the date
and place of the awarding ceremony later on an appropriate
occasion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
