<HEADLINE> Canada Requests WTO for Reprisal of Australian Salmon Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Trade Minister Sergio
Marchi appealed again Monday to the World Trade Organization (WTO)
for support of retaliation against Australia's continued salmon
ban.
</P>
<P>
Marchi accused Australia of failing to meet WTO's "July 6
deadline" to lift the long-standing ban on imports of Canadian
fresh, chilled and frozen salmon.
</P>
<P>
"The WTO has ruled twice in our favor" Marchi said. Citing a
1998 WTO rule, the minister pointed out that Australia's ban for
fish health protection "clearly has no scientific basis."
</P>
<P>
Canada is seeking authority to impose a 100 percent surtax on
imports of certain Australian products, the minister said, adding
"Under the WTO rules, Canada has until August 5 to request this
authority." 
</P>
</TEXT>
