<HEADLINE> Congo (K) Conflict to Be On Agenda of 35th OAU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) Salim Ahmed Salim has said
that the conflict in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) will
be on the agenda of the 35th OAU Summit in Algerian capital
Algiers from July 12 to 14.
</P>
<P>
"If we manage to resolve the conflict in the DRC, we shall be
encouraged to make further efforts to find solutions to the other
conflicts tearing our continent apart,'' Salim said Sunday upon
arrival from Zambia where he had participated in the discussions
on Congo (K) peace with ministers of relevant countries.
</P>
<P>
The secretary-general noted that collective efforts are
required from all OAU member states to put an end to conflicts and
terrorism, which constitute a "threat to the stability and
security of states and and their peoples."
</P>
<P>
Salim said he is optimistic about the outcome of the current
talks in Lusaka by the ministers to end the 11-month war in the
vast central African country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a sub-committee set up by the ministers worked late
into the early hours of Monday morning to finish all documents to
be adopted by the ministers at a plenary session later.
</P>
<P>
The adoption of the draft pact would be followed by a heads of
state signing ceremony with the date yet to be announced.
</P>
<P>
Salim also expressed satisfaction with the work done by the
Algerian government to prepare for the OAU Summit.
</P>
<P>
He underscored the need for increased economic cooperation
among African member states so as to meet the challenges of
globalization in the coming millennium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
